Package navmid.graph

The midlet navigation graph described by its "menagerie" of nodes.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
ActionNode Represents an action in a midlet (either changing the current screen or performing a Security Relevant Method).
CallbackNode A CallbackNode represents a callback method in a listener class (abstracted by a ListenerClassNode.
CommandNode This class describes an abstract command object allocated at a given point.
Context This class describes an execution context for a callback.
DisplayableNode Class describing the screen contents which are the main nodes of the navigation graphs (other nodes are build artefacts).
IntNode Represents the potential values of an integer variable used as an attribute to an abstract object.
ItemNode Abstract nodes representing LCDUI item objects.
ListenerAssociationNode A listener association node is a graph node created between a screen node and a class implementing the event listener functionality (which may be used for several screen nodes).
ListenerClassNode This node represents an implementation of a listener node.
ListenerNode A listener node is an abstraction of a dynamic object implementing an event listener.
Node The basic class for nodes.
ObjectNode An Object Node is a node of the graph corresponding to an abstraction of live Java objects.
PathNode Represents a path in a callback.
StringNode  
TestNode Represents a parsable test on a path for which we can safely approximate the result.
TransitionNode A synthetic transition associated to a displayable.
 

Enum Summary
ActionNode.ActionKind Enumeration describing the kind of action node considered.
CallbackNode.Event Enumeration listing all the kinds of events that can be treated by callbacks.
DisplayableNode.DisplayableKind This enumeration defines the state represented by a Displayable object.
ItemNode.ItemKind Enumeration specifying the kind of lcdui item.
Node.Kind An enumeration listing the kind (purpose) of graph nodes.
TestNode.TestKind This enumeration lists the tests handled by the analyzer and that can help to prune the list of paths extracted with the points-to analyis and the local path analysis.
 

Package navmid.graph Description

The midlet navigation graph described by its "menagerie" of nodes.
